If it isn't my little Tess.

1005
01:55:28,100 --> 01:55:31,440
Oh poor poppet. What a state you are in.

1006
01:55:33,200 --> 01:55:35,200
You are so cold!

1007
01:55:41,160 --> 01:55:44,210
Here. Get that inside you

1008
01:55:44,840 --> 01:55:46,210
This will warm your bones

1009
01:55:49,010 --> 01:55:50,760
Go on my love. Drink it.

1010
01:56:01,190 --> 01:56:02,230
Get it out

1011
01:56:03,610 --> 01:56:05,570
You mustn't let yourself go.

1012
01:56:05,780 --> 01:56:07,780
Even bad luck runs out in the end.

1013
01:56:08,410 --> 01:56:09,700
Take my word for it.

1014
01:56:10,460 --> 01:56:11,710
I can't go on.

1015
01:56:12,250 --> 01:56:14,040
You'll feel better tomorrow.

1016
01:56:14,500 --> 01:56:19,180
OH no. I can't go on. My life...

1017
01:56:22,470 --> 01:56:25,430
If I had the courage, I'd like to die.

1018
01:56:26,150 --> 01:56:28,440
Don't talk such flubbery.

1019
01:56:29,610 --> 01:56:31,690
Why didn't you come and see me sooner?

1020
01:56:33,030 --> 01:56:34,610
Eh? I could have taken you in here, my girl.

1021
01:56:35,070 --> 01:56:35,990
Is there still some work here.

1022
01:56:36,330 --> 01:56:38,160
In this wretched place?

1023
01:56:39,410 --> 01:56:42,370
There's always work here.

1024
01:56:52,770 --> 01:56:55,390
Come... have some
of my nice soup.

1025
01:57:01,440 --> 01:57:05,530
After that, we must
take off those slum,

1026
01:57:06,080 --> 01:57:09,710
mirky clothes and
prettify yourself. Eh?

1027
01:57:17,090 --> 01:57:19,970
Just to make me jealous again, hey?

1028
01:57:22,810 --> 01:57:23,890
WEll, Tessy.

1029
01:58:46,590 --> 01:58:47,640
Are you the new hand?

1030
01:58:57,280 --> 01:58:59,780
T'was you was it?

1031
01:59:03,030 --> 01:59:04,580
Is that all you've done?

1032
01:59:05,450 --> 01:59:07,000
T'is a mighty poor show.

1033
01:59:07,540 --> 01:59:09,080
She's not accustomed to it.

1034
01:59:09,250 --> 01:59:10,830
I don't keep useless hands here.

1035
01:59:11,380 --> 01:59:12,630
I'm not payed for what we do.

1036
01:59:12,920 --> 01:59:14,340
So where's the difference?

1037
01:59:14,510 --> 01:59:15,300
No arguing.

1038
01:59:15,510 --> 01:59:16,890
I want the whole lot cleared.

1039
01:59:17,510 --> 01:59:18,180
Well, it's too late.

1040
01:59:19,720 --> 01:59:20,890
You'd better.

1041
01:59:29,780 --> 01:59:31,280
Now, you not mind Groby.

1042
01:59:32,660 --> 01:59:33,740
T'is just as well.

1043
01:59:34,290 --> 01:59:35,790
Ah... I know lord loves us.

1044
01:59:36,370 --> 01:59:37,870
but it's not like it was at the dairy.

1045
01:59:38,580 --> 01:59:40,380
Dairyman on the deck all the week,

1046
01:59:41,300 --> 01:59:43,260
On Sundays he's the Mr Richard Crick!

1047
02:00:45,640 --> 02:00:47,680
It don't do to pray here missy.

1048
02:00:51,980 --> 02:00:53,730
There's been a curse on this place.

1049
02:00:56,320 --> 02:00:57,950
This is the Cross-in-hand, isn't it?

1050
02:00:58,160 --> 02:00:59,320
Aye. So it is.

1051
02:01:00,990 --> 02:01:04,040
On the count of a malefactor
they tortured here, in ancient times

1052
02:01:04,290 --> 02:01:09,630
they did nail his hand onto the
post and then they hangged him.

1053
02:01:10,970 --> 02:01:14,800
The bones are down
there to this day I'm told.

1054
02:04:02,540 --> 02:04:03,540
OH!

1055
02:04:06,590 --> 02:04:07,460
What have you found?

1056
02:04:08,340 --> 02:04:10,140
An old pair of boots.

1057
02:04:16,440 --> 02:04:17,900
STill in good condition.

1058
02:04:21,940 --> 02:04:23,490
Could be of use to the poor.

1059
02:05:21,190 --> 02:05:22,900
There! Have a look.

1060
02:06:14,190 --> 02:06:16,440
I knew nothing of your circumstances.

1061
02:06:16,810 --> 02:06:19,820
Nothing at all until your mother wrote to me.

1062
02:06:20,030 --> 02:06:20,740
My mother?

1063
02:06:20,990 --> 02:06:24,160
She wrote what you should
have told me a long time ago.

1064
02:06:25,870 --> 02:06:26,950
I came at once.

1065
02:06:29,630 --> 02:06:30,500
Tess...

1066
02:06:39,560 --> 02:06:40,970
Why did you never say anything?

1067
02:06:41,430 --> 02:06:43,140
I had nothing to ask of you.

1068
02:06:44,480 --> 02:06:45,400
That isn't so.

1069
02:06:47,110 --> 02:06:50,740
You wear your ridiculous pride like a h

1070
02:06:51,570 --> 02:06:54,120
And you put me even more
in the wrong than I was!

1071
02:06:55,080 --> 02:06:56,200
Against my will

1072
02:06:57,790 --> 02:06:59,960
I have done my duty for my child.

1073
02:07:01,290 --> 02:07:02,670
On my honour i did it.

1074
02:07:03,380 --> 02:07:04,510
honour...

1075
02:07:06,510 --> 02:07:08,890
I want to take you away
from this wretched place.

1076
02:07:09,260 --> 02:07:10,350
Somewhere you're worthy of.

1077
02:07:11,560 --> 02:07:16,020
What is this strange temptation
that misery holds for you?

1078
02:07:16,940 --> 02:07:18,730
Come to your senses.

1079
02:07:19,570 --> 02:07:20,650
Come away with me.

1080
02:07:26,330 --> 02:07:27,290
your father's ill.

1081
02:07:27,420 --> 02:07:28,210
Did you know?

1082
02:07:29,210 --> 02:07:29,880
yes...

1083
02:07:30,750 --> 02:07:32,800
they fear the worst.

1084
02:07:33,420 --> 02:07:36,760
your family will be evicted if he dies.

1085
02:07:39,640 --> 02:07:41,810
I'm offering you my help sincerely.

1086
02:07:43,980 --> 02:07:45,270
Noone else seems to care.

1087
02:07:47,030 --> 02:07:49,700
Who is this husband of yours?

1088
02:07:50,870 --> 02:07:52,160
How can he abandon you like this?

1089
02:07:53,330 --> 02:07:55,290
Tess!

1090
02:10:24,540 --> 02:10:28,250
There's a point beyond
which obstinity becomes stupedity.

1091
02:10:32,010 --> 02:10:34,050
Are you in love with this drudgery?

1092
02:10:37,230 --> 02:10:38,940
I may be a sham-D'Urberville

1093
02:10:39,270 --> 02:10:41,190
but my little finger can
do more for you than

1094
02:10:41,480 --> 02:10:42,820
your blue-blooded ancestors.

1095
02:10:47,070 --> 02:10:50,740
I'm right. You know I am.

1096
02:10:56,670 --> 02:10:58,510
Forget about all this

1097
02:10:59,970 --> 02:11:00,840
and forget about that mule

1098
02:11:01,300 --> 02:11:02,590
that you call your husband.

1099
02:11:07,140 --> 02:11:10,900
Go on. Hit me. I shall not cry out.

1100
02:11:12,650 --> 02:11:14,650
Once beckon...
always beckon again.

1101
02:11:15,530 --> 02:11:16,360
That's law.

1102
02:11:17,160 --> 02:11:18,200
I was your master once

1103
02:11:21,040 --> 02:11:21,790
and so shall be again.

1104
02:11:24,330 --> 02:11:27,840
If you are any man's wife,
you are mine.

1105
02:11:30,010 --> 02:11:31,260
My own dear husband.

1106
02:11:32,680 --> 02:11:35,390
I shall die soon unless
I get a word from you.

1107
02:11:36,850 --> 02:11:39,150
All my letter have
remained unanswered.

1108
02:11:41,110 --> 02:11:43,530
Have you even received them?

1109
02:11:45,570 --> 02:11:49,910
I long for one thing only.
And that is to see you again.

1110
02:11:51,250 --> 02:11:52,410
Come back to me Angel.

1111
02:11:53,790 --> 02:11:57,090
Come back to me and save me
from the thing that threatens me.

1112
02:12:33,010 --> 02:12:37,100
Any reasonable person would
call this a ludicrous situation.

1113
02:12:38,770 --> 02:12:42,440
I offered to help you.
You wanned all of that.

1114
02:12:43,860 --> 02:12:47,450
You prefer to turnyourself into gypsies.

1115
02:12:48,240 --> 02:12:48,750
Please go.

1116
02:12:49,580 --> 02:12:52,710
In other words, Mrs. Clare,
you are asking me to let

1117
02:12:52,960 --> 02:12:53,960
you starve in peace.

1118
02:12:54,210 --> 02:12:55,250
Go away!

1119
02:12:57,010 --> 02:12:58,800
You'll be civil yet.

1120
02:13:06,940 --> 02:13:09,270
What's to become of me
and my poor little mites?

1121
02:13:10,610 --> 02:13:12,570
WE be the D'Urberville family.

1122
02:13:12,820 --> 02:13:13,950
It's written there isn't it?

1123
02:13:14,410 --> 02:13:17,120
Oh yeah... it's written there
fine enough. I grant you.

1124
02:13:17,620 --> 02:13:18,870
But the rooms have been taken.

1125
02:13:19,790 --> 02:13:21,120
You never sent in your deposits.

1126
02:13:22,500 --> 02:13:25,000
He means the money to
pay for the account, mother.

1127
02:13:25,840 --> 02:13:27,800
There's more to life than money sir!

1128
02:13:28,760 --> 02:13:31,810
You can not leave these poor,
fatherless children in the streets.

1129
02:13:32,270 --> 02:13:33,140
It would be a crime!

1130
02:13:33,390 --> 02:13:33,850
Missus...

1131
02:13:34,060 --> 02:13:36,440
Hospitality is sacred,
even among the Pagan Turks!

1132
02:13:36,810 --> 02:13:38,520
Please Missus... tis your own fault.

1133
02:13:38,900 --> 02:13:39,940
We'll see about that.

1134
02:13:40,570 --> 02:13:43,160
We are a true descendents
of the knightly D'Urbervilles.

1135
02:13:43,570 --> 02:13:45,950
Nobody leaves us in
the streets like raw apples.

1136
02:13:46,200 --> 02:13:49,540
Not in the home of our ancestors.
Our boards are in the

1137
02:13:49,750 --> 02:13:51,580
crip there laid out there in their carpets.

1138
02:13:51,790 --> 02:13:52,500
what's with you...

1139
02:13:52,920 --> 02:13:56,170
No, my dear. What's true is true.
Your poor father's eyes

1140
02:13:56,470 --> 02:13:58,090
are on us. We mustn't shame him.

1141
02:13:59,510 --> 02:14:02,970
Oh lord protect his own.
On the weekly champ he punished.

1142
02:14:03,690 --> 02:14:05,020
Ladies stopping here then?

1143
02:14:05,560 --> 02:14:07,230
no my good man. we are going on.

1144
02:14:08,030 --> 02:14:09,190
Good man... good man...

1145
02:14:09,690 --> 02:14:11,990
I ought to get by to Marlott.

1146
02:14:32,640 --> 02:14:33,520
Unload Darrell.

1147
02:14:33,980 --> 02:14:34,520
Where?

1148
02:14:34,810 --> 02:14:35,230
Here!

1149
02:14:35,560 --> 02:14:36,400
Here?

1150
02:14:36,650 --> 02:14:37,270
Yes Here.

1151
02:14:37,820 --> 02:14:39,610
We shall camp beside our church

1152
02:14:40,150 --> 02:14:41,530
until the town of our ancestors,

1153
02:14:41,780 --> 02:14:42,660
Find us our shelters.

1154
02:14:43,320 --> 02:14:45,370
Now come on children.
Set to work.

1155
02:16:32,100 --> 02:16:34,230
Why am I on the
wrong side of this door?

1156
02:17:49,550 --> 02:17:50,050
Yeah!

1157
02:17:50,510 --> 02:17:52,800
It's me Father, Angel!

1158
02:18:05,400 --> 02:18:08,200
My boy, my poor boy.

1159
02:18:08,530 --> 02:18:10,740
I've been ill but I'm alright now.

1160
02:18:28,730 --> 02:18:31,650
Why have you treated me
so monstrously Angel?

1161
02:18:32,730 --> 02:18:37,360
I do not deserve it.
I have thought it over carefully

1162
02:18:38,620 --> 02:18:40,990
and I can never, never forgive you.

1163
02:18:42,290 --> 02:18:46,460
You are cruel. I shall try to forget you.

1164
02:18:47,500 --> 02:18:51,760
All I ever received of
your hands is injustice.

1165
02:20:17,170 --> 02:20:18,670
Mr Durbeyfield.

1166
02:20:21,430 --> 02:20:23,060
Beg your pardon?

1167
02:20:23,720 --> 02:20:24,770
You are Mr Durbeyfield?

1168
02:20:26,390 --> 02:20:28,480
They don't live here no more.

1169
02:20:28,650 --> 02:20:29,730
Since when?

1170
02:20:30,900 --> 02:20:32,320
Since John Durbeyfield died.

1171
02:20:33,700 --> 02:20:35,070
Do you know where they went?

1172
02:20:49,260 --> 02:20:51,970
Durbeyfield... from 1832 to 1888

1173
02:20:52,890 --> 02:20:55,560
more properly D'Urberville of once

1174
02:20:55,890 --> 02:20:56,940
powerful family of that name

1175
02:20:58,020 --> 02:21:00,230
and directly descended
through illustrious lines

1176
02:21:00,480 --> 02:21:03,990
of Pagan D'Urberville.
Likes of a conqueror.

1177
02:21:04,490 --> 02:21:05,780
How are the mighty fallen?

1178
02:21:07,410 --> 02:21:09,200
Ah yes... how indeed.

1179
02:21:09,960 --> 02:21:12,000
May I? for the poor.

1180
02:21:14,210 --> 02:21:16,000
I prefer to settle
the Mason's account.

1181
02:21:17,220 --> 02:21:19,340
You'd think he's never
been paid for his work.

1182
02:21:21,930 --> 02:21:23,140
They were an odd family.

1183
02:21:23,770 --> 02:21:25,310
My collegue Mr Tringham,
would have done

1184
02:21:25,600 --> 02:21:26,890
better to have kept his mouth shut.

1185
02:22:03,620 --> 02:22:05,910
I should like to see Mrs Clare.

1186
02:22:09,210 --> 02:22:10,000
Tess

1187
02:22:11,380 --> 02:22:13,460
Yes I know. She's not here.

1188
02:22:15,170 --> 02:22:16,510
You are Mrs. Durbeyfield.

1189
02:22:17,840 --> 02:22:18,640
Yes

1190
02:22:19,800 --> 02:22:20,720
Where is she living?

1191
02:22:21,930 --> 02:22:22,680
I don't know.

1192
02:22:24,520 --> 02:22:25,480
I'm her husband.

1193
02:22:26,610 --> 02:22:27,980
I guessed as much.

1194
02:22:29,690 --> 02:22:30,860
Then tell me where she is.

1195
02:22:31,900 --> 02:22:32,910
Please, tell me.

1196
02:22:33,280 --> 02:22:36,580
Leave her. Leave her in peace.

1197
02:22:37,450 --> 02:22:39,710
My poor girl's suffered enough.

1198
02:22:41,130 --> 02:22:44,340
She don't care to see you sir. Never.

1199
02:23:00,610 --> 02:23:02,410
Mrs Durbeyfield,

1200
02:23:03,070 --> 02:23:05,330
take pity on a lonely,
wretched man.

1201
02:23:05,490 --> 02:23:07,000
Tell me where to find her.

1202
02:23:08,710 --> 02:23:09,500
I beg you.

1203
02:23:11,630 --> 02:23:12,590
She's at Sandbourne.

1204
02:23:12,800 --> 02:23:15,170
Sandbourne? But where?

1205
02:23:15,550 --> 02:23:17,090
It's a large town these days.

1206
02:23:17,430 --> 02:23:20,180
That's all I know. Sandbourne.

1207
02:23:49,810 --> 02:23:50,680
Excuse me.

1208
02:23:51,890 --> 02:23:53,520
I'm looking for a Mrs. Clare.

1209
02:23:54,150 --> 02:23:56,190
Would you by any
chance know her address?

1210
02:23:58,990 --> 02:24:02,580
Ah, George. You got a Clare around?

1211
02:24:05,290 --> 02:24:07,750
No... we've had a lot of
visitors here. You know.

1212
02:24:08,000 --> 02:24:09,460
Or Durbeyfield. Miss Durbeyfield.

1213
02:24:09,840 --> 02:24:11,170
D'Urberville at the Herons.

1214
02:24:11,420 --> 02:24:12,090
That's it. D'Urberville.

1215
02:24:12,510 --> 02:24:14,760
It's a boarding house sir. Can't miss it.

1216
02:24:14,970 --> 02:24:15,590
Where abouts?

1217
02:25:12,800 --> 02:25:13,340
Yes?

1218
02:25:14,010 --> 02:25:15,720
Please excuse me
for calling at this hour.

1219
02:25:16,640 --> 02:25:19,480
But do you have a Teresa
D'Urberville staying in your board?

1220
02:25:19,980 --> 02:25:21,140
Mrs D'Urberville you mean?

1221
02:25:21,860 --> 02:25:22,560
Yes.

1222
02:25:23,770 --> 02:25:24,520
Please come in.

1223
02:25:30,410 --> 02:25:32,030
Would be kind enough to
tell her that her relative

1224
02:25:32,240 --> 02:25:33,120
is anxious to see her?

1225
02:25:33,450 --> 02:25:35,330
It's rather early sir. What name shall I give?

1226
02:25:35,670 --> 02:25:36,460
Angel.

1227
02:25:36,960 --> 02:25:37,670
Mr Angel?

1228
02:25:38,000 --> 02:25:40,840
Angel. It's my christian name.
She'll understand.

1229
02:25:47,810 --> 02:25:50,310
I'll go and see if she's awake.

1230
02:26:53,440 --> 02:26:57,200
Tess. I came to ask your forgiveness.

1231
02:27:01,750 --> 02:27:02,750
It's too late.

1232
02:27:04,460 --> 02:27:07,590
Too late? My darling wife.

1233
02:27:09,050 --> 02:27:10,340
I've come to fetch you.
I'm going to...

1234
02:27:11,050 --> 02:27:13,720
Don't come near me Angel please.

1235
02:27:16,640 --> 02:27:19,600
Too Late. Too Late.

1236
02:27:21,150 --> 02:27:25,610
I'm not the man I was. I've suffered too.

1237
02:27:27,950 --> 02:27:29,660
I humbly beg you to forgive me.

1238
02:27:32,370 --> 02:27:39,050
Yes. yes... But I tell you it's too late.

1239
02:27:43,680 --> 02:27:46,140
Don't you know at all? Don't you?

1240
02:27:49,150 --> 02:27:51,110
How did you find your way here?

1241
02:27:53,740 --> 02:27:54,610
I saw your mother.

1242
02:27:59,490 --> 02:28:01,080
I waited and waited for you.

1243
02:28:02,080 --> 02:28:03,000
But you didn't come.

1244
02:28:05,000 --> 02:28:06,920
I wrote to you. But you didn't come.

1245
02:28:11,390 --> 02:28:14,350
He has been good tome.
To all of us.

1246
02:28:19,060 --> 02:28:22,900
He's won me back to him.
He's upstairs.

1247
02:28:27,620 --> 02:28:30,450
Go now Angel. Go please.

1248
02:28:33,710 --> 02:28:35,750
Never come back anymore.

1249
02:30:05,590 --> 02:30:06,590
Good morning my dear

1250
02:30:21,990 --> 02:30:23,070
WEll, what's the matter now?

1251
02:30:28,120 --> 02:30:29,120
You feeling unwell?

1252
02:30:31,130 --> 02:30:32,340
Is that why you have the vapours?

1253
02:30:34,840 --> 02:30:38,930
Yes? No?

1254
02:30:42,390 --> 02:30:46,520
yes I know. You are moping as usual.

1255
02:30:50,900 --> 02:30:54,870
For god's sake, try and make an effort.

1256
02:31:02,550 --> 02:31:04,050
Did you have a bad dream?

1257
02:31:11,310 --> 02:31:12,890
Brazil perhaps?

1258
02:31:31,340 --> 02:31:34,300
These mooning hysterics
of yours are in poor taste.

1259
02:31:38,510 --> 02:31:40,470
Don't forget we are
lunching with the Bennets.

1260
02:31:41,520 --> 02:31:42,940
I'd like you to look presentable.

1261
02:31:46,110 --> 02:31:47,820
A genuine D'Urberville.

1262
02:33:59,170 --> 02:34:01,720
I came to tell you that I killed him.

1263
02:34:10,050 --> 02:34:11,220
I've done it.

1264
02:34:13,220 --> 02:34:14,270
I don't know how

1265
